CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 18, 1962, page 14, reads: "Policy - Makers - This group constitues the policy making staff of the Pennsylvania Baptist Congress of Christian Education. This is, in fact, the executive board. This board makes the policy and approves the program. In the front row are (left to right) Miss C. Ross, corresponding secretary; W. M. Stockton, vice president; Mrs. V. Valentine, recording secretary; Eustace Gay, president; Mrs. E. Venable, statistician; W. Williams, vice president at large; D. A. Delaver, assistant dean, and W. A. Arvin, dean. Other leaders, members of this board, include the district deans and directors, and others."
TitMainTitle: Men and women, staff of the Pennsylvania Baptist Congress of Christian Education, including front row, left to right: C. Ross, W. M. Stockton, Mrs. V. Valentine, Eustace Gay, Mrs. E. Venable, W. Williams, D. A. Delaver, and W. A. Arvin, seated in pews of Mt. Zion Baptist Church
